caption: Love the fajita's nice atmosphere nice and friendly place to visit the food is good
The food always hits the spot for Mexican cravings! The presentation of the food is always beautiful as well. This is a great spot for affordable excise food in the district.
Republic Cantina is a neighborhood gem! Their food, ambience and customer service is top notch and their happy hours specials make me want to shop up at 3:50 daily.

I absolutely loved this place. The service is great and polite, the food actually has flavor and it’s fresh! I had the avocado toast Benedict if I remember the name correctly and the blueberry pancakes and it was soo fresh and so tasty! I also had the pumpkin spice latte and it was 💯 !

Fantastic neighborhood Tex Mex spot! Placed an order here for pick up tonight. Only took 19 minutes from time of order to when it was ready and we received text messages along the way. The staff was super helpful and the food was fresh, delicious (e.g., the brisket in the brisket enchiladas was tender and perfectly flavorful), and generously portioned.
Long waiting time!

All of your TexMex cravings will be solved at Republic Cantina. The queso is literally to die for and their margaritas are the best in town! The service is always delightful which is a olus. From cocktails to coffee, their menu has an option for everyone!

Look man.... Get the 3 Taco dinner/sampler that's all you need to know. Those tacos are fire. They are really good and filling, there is no shortage of meat in these tacos. The customer service was fantastic. It is recommended to order online, but I assure you if you get that 3 taco dinner you will not be disappointed. You don't know me but trust me on this one.
fire food but a small patio and limited seating. really great service however. drinks are awesome.
Great food, drinks and atmosphere.

I love this restaurant! Having moved to DC from Houston in 2019, discovering this restaurant a couple weeks after the move made me less homesick. I can't say enough good things about it - from the blue-and-white tile street sign (reminiscent of the ones in Houston) and wonderful atmosphere, to the amazing food (the queso is simply wow) and inventive drinks (shoutout to the Pico Back shot) - I just love this place. I try to get breakfast tacos once a week during the pandemic to show my support, and they're always a bright spot in my week. Their coffee is delicious too!
Good coffee, banging breakfast tacos, be sure to not skimp on the spicy margaritas. Would recommend, and outdoor dining is 👌🏻

We came for a patio dinner on a Friday night and it was so good we came back for brunch on Sunday! The margaritas were exactly what I wanted and everyone should try the surprisingly delightful Pico Back Shot. We ordered a little bit of everything for both meals and especially liked the tostada's, queso, and fajitas (dinner) and tacos & chilaquiles (brunch) were perfect.  Cute outdoor space with heaters, great drinks & food, fun staff.
I love this place! Perfect ambiance for a casual but delicious meal. The service and food were both amazing!

Came here for brunch and it did not disappoint! The cappuccino was perfection and food was delicious!  (Pupusas were amazing) The decor is adorable inside but there is plenty of seating out front or on the side patio with heat lamps.  DC desperately needed a Tex-Mex restaurant and this is done so well.  Can’t wait to come back for lunch or dinner!
Feel like I'm deep in the heart of texas in NE
Being a Texas ex-pat, I'm sad to see you go. I hope you have success in your next venture because the east coast needs more kolaches and breakfast tacos
Please come to this place! You’ll be treated like a true Rey de España! Tracy, the bar manager, is awesome. We came here for a birthday and it was great!! Juan José (JJ) is great too!
Great breakfast tacos!

Visited here with their takeout only menu on the patio and was so impressed by their service and food quality! We were craving their the nachos. Unfortunately, they are currently not on the menu due to travel concerns. However, the kitchen obliged and whipped up some just for us! Best nachos...even in takeout containers. Thanks for making our night!
Excellent Tex-Mex and charming digs nestled in a lovely DC neighborhood.
Lovely experience, friendly staff and tasty food. Patio dining is a must. Highly recommend brisket enchiladas!

We didn't get to try this place. We showed up and they couldn't seat us because they were booked. They tried to accommodate us by allowing us to order food and said they would set up some chairs on the sidewalk but we'd have to eat on our laps. I appreciated the effort, but I need a table and the neighborhood they are in is a bit strange. (There was a half-naked dude hanging out on a balcony overlooking the sidewalk.) We decided to go elsewhere. I can't speak to the food, but their service was excellent. If I was in town longer I'd definitely make a reservation and try again.
best fajitas I ever had
Amazing breakfast. Highly recommend. Since they can only have outdoor seating, definitely suggest getting a reservation.
I ordered takeout tonight. They texted to confirm & when it was ready. Super fast and tasty too. I will definitely be back
Tried smoked pork tacos and fajitas: delicious! Nice spot with terrace.
Best queso on DC! Super friendly staff.
They have the best tacos. Periodt
Oh my gosh! I had such a great brisket enchilada at Republic Cantina 😋
Amazing food, service, and ambiance.

Great option for COVID carry out - in particular, the par-cooked flour tortillas puff up and brown beautifully in the pan at home. We’ve ordered fajitas and then had breakfast tacos for a couple of days afterward (they will also sell you some tasty eggs).

The food was pretty standard, but we were less impressed by the two $20 margaritas we received. Upon calling the restaurant to inquire if we received only one by mistake and would be refunded for it, Tracy was extremely rude.  One star for bad service.
Tasty food with a really lovely vibe. Got the chilaquiles which were fantastic! Definitely a good southwestern/Texan ambiance hidden in Washington, DC. Go on a sunny day for the best experience.
Fantastic breakfast taco spot.  Try the Migas.
Great breakfast taco and habanero salsa
Good tex-mex style tacos. Nice people. Good coffee.
Awesome spicy margaritas!! Cheese enchiladas are the best!

Fabulous breakfast tacos, quick service, and a clean venue. I've been here several times and I've always enjoyed the quiet atmosphere. They also have a great weekend happy hour special menu. Unfortunately at the time of this review they don't have their liquor license to serve during the week. Great neighborhood place if you're in the NoMa area.
Really good food and drinks, not a ton of money

Republic Cantina is such a great spot! Definitely a great place to stop and get a coffee and relax. The food is wonderful and Angela was an outstanding barista. We loved the food and coffee and will absolutely be back soon.

This place is so fantastic. We loved everything we ordered. The complimentary salsa, the margaritas, the guac, the tacos and the fajitas. All delicious. Great atmosphere — would definitely recommend to all my mexican food lovers.
It was delicious. Thanks. Great service.
Food ok, cocktails were pretty decent.  In general everything was expecting alright

Absolutely love everything about this place. The atmosphere, the staff was wildly friendly and helpful and concerned with how our visit was going. The food was all great. Possibly the best steak fajitas we've ever had. The salsa is also one of the best, and I loved trying different drinks. Will definitely be back.
Really good kolaches and coffee!

Food is terrific! There really aren't any Tex Mex options in DC so it fills a necessary restaurant void. Queso and flour tortillas are AMAZING. It is sliiiightly overpriced but that hasn't stopped me from going 5+ times since it opened last year. Highly recommend!
I'm on the wall of supporters here and I consider it money well spent. I don't come here as much as I would like to but I've never had a bad time and the food is delicious
Perfect place to bring a family. Tacos and cinnamon rolls over a game of candy land. The ideal Saturday morning.

Stumbled upon this neighborhood restaurant and was pleasantly surprised. The full service coffee bar, and breakfast menu was delightful. The in house hot sauce was also v good!  Looking forward to returning for the dinner menu, and the Carmel Brûlée cappuccino.

The food is amazing but the service is really slow and not helpful. Looked at my food sit there for ten minutes before I received it. Also not the cleanest place. The bathroom smelled so strongly of urine that I almost got sick.
Great little Tex-Mex place.  Really a coffee shop/bar with an awesome food menu. Went for breakfast and planning to go back for dinner. Highly recommend the brisket kolache.

This is fast becoming one of my favorite restaurants in DC! I've been for dinner and for the cafe-style breakfast. Republic Cantina hits all the marks: friendly and great service, gorgeous interior (which partially opens up to the outdoors on nice days which is super pleasant), and amazing food and drink. I'm a vegetarian and have plenty of options here- I had fajitas for dinner and the chilaquiles for breakfast (pictured). Margaritas are great and the latte with cajeta is INSANE. Such a great establishment to have in the neighborhood!
a MUST visit spot for the best ‘Tex Mex’ cuisine in D.C ! I’ve always gotten the fajitas and impressed each time by the homemade tortillas & great service. The atmosphere is intimate & unique

The staff was very friendly. I live in the neighborhood and finally decided to go in one night. I was talked into trying the debut of a taco salad. I paid 13 dollars for a brisket salad, but wheres the beef?  There was plenty of lettuce though. Tried it. Wont do it again The 3 stars ate for the friendly staff and the nice atmosphere. Also, I ordered my food to go anf thr barely found a bag and they gave me no utensils.

Amazing local neighborhood place - I had one of my favorite meals in DC here. I stared with a delicious margarita, then has the cheese dip which was also great. The fajitas are the star of the meal - flavorful and you get to choose two types of meat, which allows for nice variety. Great place - worth the trip a little bit off the beaten path.
Great food but they never answer the phone so you can't order ahead.
Delicious place. 4 Californians loved it. Awesome food and service.
A true good food restaurant.  Great tacos and delicious kolachis with a nice selection of beverages.

We were in DC for the night looking for something close by. Service was good, that’s about it. Food was god awful and over priced. Got the threeway tostadas, brisket wasn’t bad/ceviche was like rancid feet. Enchiladas poblano was basically runny soup with no tortillas anywhere to be found and hardly any chicken. Dude was nice enough to toss a couple shots of house tequila for the wait but gave us a chaser of some pickled juice that tasted like fermented orangutan piss. Find something authentic don’t waste your time or money here

Updated as of (12/8): Came in for brunch and was welcomed with awesome updates. The restaurant has transitioned to reusable cups and flatware as primary and one-use plastic as secondary. The staff were extremely welcoming and kind. Additionally, the new tortilla recipe is really good. Looking forward to many more successful years for Sam and team. Definitely Truxton Circle's flagship restaurant.  Food is very solid but the customer service is a work in progress. We ordered tacos and an iced coffee. The restaurant defaults to giving customers plastic cups for in-restaurant drink orders. When my girlfriend asked if we could have the iced coffee in a glass, Luis at the register begrudgingly remarked, "it would be helpful if you brought your own glass."  Behind him were multiple glasses that he could use. Luis was unexpectedly demeaning and made us feel unwelcomed. Republic Cantina is a nice addition to the neighborhood, but the restaurant's environmental responsibility and customer experience have significant room for improvement.

As a Texpat, I wholeheartedly recommend their breakfast tacos! Best this side of Austin. Excellent tortillas that you can taste are made in house. Although I love their brunch menu, I was a little disappointed when I went for dinner. The drinks were great, but the queso was grainy and many of the entrees were a bit underwhelming and kind of pricey. If I go again for dinner, I’ll stick with the fajitas given how tasty the tortillas are. But either way I definitely still love their breakfast tacos and regularly return for those !
Living in Houston for 4 years, I am so thankful to have found this restaurant for some real- deal Tex-Mex!  Amazing restaurant—Shout out to Suzy for great service!
Delicious breakfast tacos and coffee! Decor makes it feel homey and retro.

Such a great little spot! A very chill Tex-Mex joint in Truxton Circle. My boyfriend and I came here on a Saturday evening and were seated right away.  We started with the cider, shrimp torta and then ordered the fajitas. Food-wise, everything was amazing from start to finish. Really loved the complimentary chips and salsa and the torta tasted really fresh.  The cider drink was hot and didn’t taste too strongly of whiskey. I don’t like whiskey as much as I used to so I was really glad about this!  The fajitas. OMG. So good. We ordered the chicken, pork shoulder and shrimp fajitas. Highly recommend. The tortillas were excellent as well.  Only docking a star because the service was rather sporadic and our waiter disappeared for quite some time and never came over to our table between the appetizer and the ordering of the main meal. The table wasn’t bussed until our main food was delivered.
Delicious food! Delicious coffee drinks! Great drink menu! Great space! Cool spot to chill! Must check out
Quaint neighborhood Tex Mex place. Small place in a DC row house. Excellent food and tasty, boozey margaritas
Fantastic
Queso compuesto is a must paired with a spicy margarita! Fajitas and chicken fried steak are also delicious.
Hidden gem in DC. The food is fresh and the flavor is original. The chips and salsa is amazing. The decor is really nice and modern. They have a great selection of soft and hard drinks. Must try!
All I can say is BREAKFAST TACOS! This place is so charming and the food is excellent. You have to go!
Good food for where it's at. Remember this is DC, not Texas.
Special place, special night. Tracy, Susie, etc. all treated us so well. Tres leches cake awesome, fajitas solid. Tortillas house made. I'm from SATX so TexMex at my heart. Will return.
Delicious food, great service and super cute decor! Recommended!
Amazing. Great vibe and style, tacos were to die for, coffee was delicious, and the staff was very friendly!

I give this place 5 stars in DC, but not in Texas. But really,  this is some of the better Tex Mex food I've had on the East coast. We came here to watch the world series game 4 and found a gold mine of Astro fans in DC. The place was packed and hectic but awesome all at the same time. It was definitely an experience and I would recommend this place.
This place is great! Awesome salsa, Texas wine, and superb nachos! Came to watch the Astros World Series game and would come back.
The food was very good but it's hard to hear when its crowded as the place is very small.
Cool tacos, cool space

Amazing neighborhood Tex-Mex joint. Super friendly staff and wonderful food options. Great for breakfast/brunch and dinner (I've never been for lunch). Delicious cocktails, and affordable prices. Hit it up for sure if you are in the neighborhood and even if you aren't, it's worth the trip.
Brisket enchiladas and banana dessert were excellent
Delicious and cute ambience
Breakfast tacos are really great
Awesome staff, great space, and fantastic food.

Delicious breakfast tacos - my favorites are the bacon, the chorizo, and the brisket. Pretty accommodating to babies, just wish they had a changing table in the bathrooms, but the bathrooms are small. Best time to come with baby and a stroller is before 9am or after 12:30 pm on the weekends.

My undeniable new favorite coffee shop. Gorgeous, rustic interior, helpful and friendly staff, and WOW delicious coffee. If you love yourself at all (or you need to learn how), order the carjeta latte. I downed it before thinking to take a picture of its pretty face because it was the best caffeinated beverage I’ve ever had. I can’t wait to come back for dinner and drinks!
Terrible food, poor service. Drinks were bad, steak and chicken was so overcooked they weren't edible. Service was slow and inattentive. Prices are high and do not reflect the value.
Sorry but this place is garbage, the horchata was the most disappointing thing on here, this is more like a hipster spot.
Amazing!! Only care for breakfast so far, but the tacos are legit. The kolache was also yum! Can’t wait to come back for dinner.
The dinner menu is limited for now but good

We came on Labor Day with our 2 year old. It was busy and we first grabbed a table outside but later snagged a table inside. None of the umbrellas were open but it didn’t matter. We wanted to be out of the sun, inside. They have about 3 high chairs and there are toys available for little ones. The food was okay. Not bad but I wouldn’t drive across town for it. The service was exceptional as far as assisting us with our kid.

Wonderful restaurant that recently opened. The decor is beautiful and the tacos were delicious. I can't wait to return once they begin serving lunch and dinner options. Currently, they only have breakfast menu items.
Food and staff were great! Really cool building and environment as well.
Best Tex-Mex in DMV by far! Great fajitas! Get the sausage, you will not be disappointed. Good vibe,  no regrets.

ADDENDUM: Went back for their dinner service and was not disappointed. Fermented spicy margarita was great, and the queso was proper Texas queso. Husband got the carne guisada enchiladas and I got the brisket enchiladas. Both were really tasty and the portions were generous. I tend to judge Tex-Mex by the guac and they passed with flying colors. Simple ingredients and very flavorful.  We'll definitely be back.  Delicious breakfast tacos. Egg and brisket was really tasty. Pecan cream cheese kolache also really yummy. Bought six more kolaches to take to the office. Decor and ambiance was great. Looking forward to coming back for dinner soon.
Chorizo breakfast tacos were amazing!
Great coffee & breakfast tacos. Cant wait to go back in the ev3ning
Great new neighborhood TexMex place! Just started a dinner menu too

Delicious Tex-Mex food! Being from Texas, it was like eating tacos and kolaches back home. Full of yum. They have two types of hot sauce: mild & hot. The mild sauce was very flavourful. Best of all, their flour tortillas were awesome! So delicious. We want to return just for their flour tortillas (corn tortillas are available too upon request). Also, the service was very friendly and the place is clean
Where do I start? Great food and service
Best breakfast tacos
The fajitas are perfect.
Very tasty food, no matter what time of day. The best breakfast tacos I've ever had. Their Kolaches and cinnamon rolls are amazing. Their new dinner menu did not disappoint. Will definitely return!
Best breakfast tacos in DC

Dinner here was great. Get excited Truxton Circle! We had the fortune to participate in one of their pre-opening dinners which featured chips and salsa (with optional queso), margaritas (spicy, classic, etc.), tostados, burrito skillets and fajitas. We crushed the chips and salsa quickly - were delicious and high quality. Our margaritas were expertly mixed. The tostada was tasty and a decent size that was shareable. The chicken fajitas were really good - portion generous - and came out sizzling! My favorite however, was the enchilada skillet - 3 homemade fluffy tortillas in a skillet with gooey cheese across all three. We stuffed ourselves and didn't leave room for dessert, which looked incredible. Specifically, the banana bread pudding ice cream concoction we saw the table next to us receive and promptly devour. This is a high quality place that was done properly. We finally have a place around the corner to enjoy and proudly share with guests from other areas. It has taken a while but has been worth the wait.
Tacos are fantastic with lots of flavor and good spice. We loved the carne guisada and chorizo the most.  Also the interior design on this place is so pleasant. Just love the atmosphere.
Tacos, ambiance, service, and concept are AMAZING! I'll be a regular ;)
As a Texan, the  food was great. Had the cheese & onion enchiladas. The kolaches are the best I’ve had.
I got a Texicano, which was a shot of espresso with Dr. Pepper. It was really good! My wife was a big fan of her bacon and egg breakfast tacos. The Dr. Pepper was the REAL stuff straight from Texas.
Delicious breakfast tacos and kolaches.
So good. They are extremely nice and attentive. We enjoyed ourselves and will definitely be back!
Great breakfast tacos and coffee

”It's heresy to believe that an establishment would consider itself Tex-Mex when they put tater tots in their potato and egg breakfast tacos.” - Davey Crockett  If the menu listed ingredients that would be good. First time I've ever had onions in my bacon and egg taco; had I known I would have asked for it without it.  Also, corn chips in a carne guisada taco....nombreeee ... The best part was the fresh flour tortillas. I'll be back to try more soon. I hope there's intention to eventually extend service to include a lunch and dinner menu! This place has great potential.  #nativetexan

Breakfast tacos are tremendous and good beverage selection too with hot/cold coffees, agua fresca and more.  Prices are a little higher then you might expect if your from Texas, but they are using high quality ingredients and its DC.  Excited for them to expand their hours and menu to lunch and dinner.
A little piece of Austin in DC! As a native Texan, it’s great to have a solid migas & breakfast taco option in DC! Easy to tell the tortillas are made in-house (delicious) and excellent salsa.
Friendly staff, great coffee.
Excellent breakfast tacos and kolaches
Great take on Tex-mex in DC! Breakfast tacos and kolaches are yummy! Y’all should check it out!!
Finally some good tex-mex in the DMV!
Excellent breakfast tacos and coffee, friendly and reasonably fast service.  I’m a fan of Republic Kolache and glad to see the owners expand into a brick and mortar restaurant.

Truly disappointing. I’d been waiting to try the food of this place for months and was frankly let down by what I found. There’s nothing Mexican (or, dare I say, even Tex Mex) about this. Their concept of a licuado is nothing but a smoothie (NOT the same thing, people). Their tacos don’t have any real taste. Their chorizo is mere sausage that is barely seasoned. Also, I found a black hair on my eggs. And their “horchata” is nothing but milk with sugar. Will not be coming back. If you like Mexican food, please save your money.  Gracias, bye.
Awesome atmosphere, great staff and delicious food. I felt like I was in Texas with the Kolaches and breakfast tacos! Well done!!

I went for their pre-opening event and was absolutely delighted by the tacos - SO GOOD! I untraditionally paired these with a delicious iced coffee, because: summer. They were still sorting out their food delivery system, so there were some delays - but their customer service and the general fun vibe more than made up for it. I can't wait to come back now, to a full menu.
Great tacos, great coffee

The breakfast tacos here are delicious! The eggs were perfectly cooked and they have a good hot sauce here too, a little garlicky and medium spicy. I ordered the potato and egg taco and the chorizo and egg taco, two tacos were a good amount of food, though I could have probably stuffed one more in. I also tried the Mexicano coffee and Coca-Cola combo, it’s surprisingly good, skeptics should give it a shot!  The ambiance is nice here, great AC for the summer time and comfortable seating. I’m sure when the weather cools off and when they open for dinner outdoor seating will be great. Overall great visit!
great coffee, drinks, atmosphere and really friendly and cool staff

Definitely the best breakfast tacos I’ve had in DC, possibly anywhere. Amazing flour tortillas, fluffy eggs, perfectly prepared fillings. Cool atmosphere and friendly staff. The homemade hot sauce in little plastic containers is to die for - please sell it! Looking forward to trying dinner once it’s available.

This is one of the best new restaurants to come into the neighborhood. I agree completely with the previous reviewer the tacos are the best! Also the cajeta late is now my favorite drink to have in the morning.  Overall Review: Must go check out!

The tacos are absolutely exceptional. Have been two mornings in a row! I can’t think of a place in dc that even does breakfast tacos but the republic cantina takes me straight back to Texas.  The place has a wonderful vibe with lots of very personalized decor, cacti everywhere. I expect it to be a very welcome addition to the neighborhood.
